.TH GREET_TOOL 1 "December 2024" "Greeter" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
greet_tool \- localized greeting demo
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B greet_tool
.RI [ --name " NAME" ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B greet_tool
utility prints a localized greeting. It links against the shared library
.B libgreeter
which provides the actual message formatting.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -n , " --name "
Provide a name to greet. If omitted, a generic greeting is used.
.TP
.BR -h , " --help "
Show usage information.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B LANG
Selects the locale used to look up translations. For example:
.BR "LANG=ru_RU.UTF-8 greet_tool --name Ada" .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/locale/*/LC_MESSAGES/greeter.mo
Translation catalogs installed with the project.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gettext (1)
